BM   hmmbuild  -o /dev/null HMM SEED
SM   hmmsearch -Z 90746521 -E 1000 --cpu 8 HMM pfamseq
TP   Family
CL   CL0165
CC   This entry represents an N-terminal sensor domain (approximately
CC   29-143 residues) found in histidine kinases and related signal
CC   transduction proteins. Histidine kinases are part of two-component
CC   regulatory systems that sense environmental stimuli and phosphorylate
CC   response regulators. The family shows structural similarity to SMP_2
CC   and CHASE8 domains in clan CL0165. It is found in
CC   Thermodesulfobacteriota (Magnetococcaceae, Magnetococcales,
CC   Magnetococcia) and Pseudomonadota (Gammaproteobacteria,
CC   Alphaproteobacteria, Rhodospirillales).
